definition.value: The volume enclosed within the membrane of a transport vesicle.
The side (leaflet) of a plasma membrane that faces the cytoplasm, and all proteins embedded in it or attached to its surface.

label.value: external side of mycolate outer membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the mycolate outer membrane that faces the environment and any proteins embedded in it or loosely bound to its surface.

label.value: internal side of mycolate outer membrane

definition.value: The side of the mycolate outer membrane that faces the cell wall peptidoglycan. It is rich in long-chain mycolic acids (hydroxylated branched-chain fatty acids) that are covalently linked to the cell wall peptidoglycan via an arabinogalactan network.

label.value: stromal side of plastid inner membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the plastid inner membrane that faces the stroma, and any proteins embedded in it or loosely bound to its surface.

label.value: lumenal side of plastid thylakoid membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the plastid thylakoid membrane that faces the lumen, and any proteins embedded in it or loosely bound to its surface.

label.value: stromal side of plastid thylakoid membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the plastid thylakoid membrane that faces the stroma, and any proteins embedded in it or loosely bound to its surface.

The component of the mitochondrial membrane consisting of the gene products that have some covalently attached part (e.g. peptide sequence or GPI anchor) which spans or is embedded in one or both leaflets of the membrane.
The side (leaflet) of the lysosomal membrane that faces the cytoplasm.
The side (leaflet) of the lysosomal membrane that faces the lumen.
Any side (leaflet) of a membrane that faces the lumen of an organelle.
A sex chromosome that has been inactivated.

label.value: condensed chromatin of inactivated sex chromosome

definition.value: A condensed form of chromatin that is associated with an inactivated sex chromosome and which is responsible for its inactivation.
A sex chromosome that has not been inactivated.
Chromatin that is part of an active sex chromosome.

A secretory organelle of a host cell, some 50 nm in diameter, of presynaptic nerve terminals -  accumulates in high concentrations of neurotransmitters and secretes these into the synaptic cleft by fusion with the 'active zone' of the presynaptic plasma membrane.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a host synaptic vesicle.
The lipid bilayer that forms the outer-most layer of an organelle.
A membrane that is a part of a larger membrane.  Examples include the apical region of the plasma membrane of an epithelial cell and the various regions of the endoplasmic reticulum membrane.
A membrane that is a (regional) part of the plasma membrane.

label.value: external side of apical plasma membrane

definition.value: The leaflet the apical region of the plasma membrane that faces away from the cytoplasm and any proteins embedded or anchored in it or attached to its surface.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of apical plasma membrane

definition.value: The side (leaflet) of the apical region of the plasma membrane that faces the cytoplasm.

A cup shaped specialization of the cytoskeleton that forms a thin layer located just below the apical mass of mature mucin secretory granules in the cytoplasm of goblet cells of the intestinal epithelium.  It consists of an orderly network of intermediate filaments and microtubules. Microtubules are arranged vertically, like barrel staves, along the inner aspect of the theta. Intermediate filaments form two networks -  an inner, basketlike network and an outer series of circumferential bundles resembling the hoops of a barrel.
A secretory granule that contains mucin.
The space between the membrane of an oocyte and a surrounding membranous structure (zona pellucida or perivitelline membrane).
Catalysis of a hydrolase reaction that removes a palmitoyl moiety from some substrate.
